## 3. Load Trained LoRA
```python
import torch
from diffusers import StableDiffusionPipeline

# Load the trained model
model_path = '/content/drive/MyDrive/path_to_your_model/master_ns_lora.safetensors'
model = torch.load(model_path)
```

## 4. Setup Pipeline
```python
pipe = StableDiffusionPipeline.from_pretrained(model_path)
```

## 5. Test Prompts
```python
prompts = [
    'A character portrait, fantasy style.',
    'A mythical creature in a forest.',
    'A serene landscape during sunset.',
    'A detailed portrait of a warrior standing proudly. '
]
```

## 6. Generate Images
```python
import random

for prompt in prompts:
    image = pipe(prompt).images[0]
    image.save(f'/content/drive/MyDrive/outputs/{prompt.replace(" ", "_").replace(",", "").replace(":", "")}.png')
```

## 7. Display Results
```python
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import os

for filename in os.listdir('/content/drive/MyDrive/outputs/'):
    img = plt.imread(f'/content/drive/MyDrive/outputs/{filename}')
    plt.imshow(img)
    plt.title(filename)
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.show()
```

## 8. Quality Assessment
- Visual evaluation checklist:
